The paper deals with graph separation problems and minimum cut problems, which are classic topics in computer science. The use of parameterized complexity and FPT algorithms suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-categories. The paper also discusses connections with weighted variants of directed cut problems and the Chain $\ell$-SAT problem, which are related to graph theory and combinatorics, indicating that the paper may also belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-categories. Finally, the use of flow-guided branching and the concept of important multi-budgeted separators suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category.
